`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The `typeof null === "object"` gotcha is the most common bug in type guards — always guard `entity !== null` separately before checking `"campfire" in entity`. The `in` operator also throws on primitives, so the primitive check must come first. This 3-step pattern (`object check → null check → property check`) is the correct order.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

